There was a worker fixing the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality I was editing "Unstoppable."
Oh, if only this damned file would open. (OneDrive is such a piece of crap.)
*Hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the sound was super loud. Great.
I turned the air purifier to the maximum setting, which felt a bit too aggressive, but I actually smelled wood shavings, so it was justified. Plus, he opposed wearing masks. And I really do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't sleep until he leaves.
The good news is that Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter 5 is very long and makes me super anxious. Yay! It's so exciting.
Looking for and replacing… ➡️ ellipsis, there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But I still have to stick to this. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally charged.
The floor repairman is using a vacuum cleaner, hoping this means he's about to finish.
He went out (it sounds like) cutting something. I sneakily glanced at the progress. There's still a lot of work left :(
Chapter 5 still has 7 pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in pretty good shape, mainly just some formatting adjustments and minor tweaks to active voice and conciseness. But I really need to take a break, have a cup of tea, and that guy is still messing around in my kitchen.
He started vacuuming again. Hoping this is a good sign.
The kitchen floor repairman is gone!
He told me he quoted the price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord is too cheap and only willing to pay for the damaged area by the entrance. It feels better.
I'm drinking tea in the garden, and the air purifier in the kitchen is working hard to purify the air in the room!
